 in base branch: <b>dev</b></p>\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  Vulnerability Details\n<p>  \n  \nPicomatch is a glob matcher written JavaScript. Versions prior to 4.0.4, 3.0.2, and 2.3.2 are vulnerable to a method injection vulnerability affecting the \"POSIX_REGEX_SOURCE\" object. Because the object inherits from \"Object.prototype\", specially crafted POSIX bracket expressions (e.g., \"[[:constructor:]]\") can reference inherited method names. These methods are implicitly converted to strings and injected into the generated regular expression. This leads to incorrect glob matching behavior (integrity impact), where patterns may match unintended filenames. The issue does not enable remote code execution, but it can cause security-relevant logic errors in applications that rely on glob matching for filtering, validation, or access control. All users of affected \"picomatch\" versions that process untrusted or user-controlled glob patterns are potentially impacted. This issue is fixed in picomatch 4.0.4, 3.0.2 and 2.3.2. Users should upgrade to one of these versions or later, depending on their supported release line. If upgrading is not immediately possible, avoid passing untrusted glob patterns to picomatch. Possible mitigations include sanitizing or rejecting untrusted glob patterns, especially those containing POSIX character classes like \"[[:...:]]\"; avoiding the use of POSIX bracket expressions if user input is involved; and manually patching the library by modifying \"POSIX_REGEX_SOURCE\" to use a null prototype.\n\n<p>Publish Date: 2026-03-26\n<p>URL: <a href=https://www.mend.io/vulnerability-database/CVE-2026-33672>CVE-2026-33672</a></p>\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  CVSS 3 Score Details (<b>5.3</b>)\n<p>\n\nBase Score Metrics:\n- Exploitability Metrics:\n  - Attack Vector: Network\n  - Attack Complexity: Low\n  - Privileges Required: None\n  - User Interaction: None\n  - Scope: Unchanged\n- Impact Metrics:\n  - Confidentiality Impact: None\n  - Integrity Impact: Low\n  - Availability Impact: None\n</p>\nFor more information on CVSS3 Scores, click <a href=\"https://www.first.org/cvss/calculator/3.0\">here</a>.\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n###  Suggested Fix\n<p>\n\n<p>Type: Upgrade version</p>\n<p>Release Date: 2026-03-25</p>\n<p>Fix Resolution: https://github.com/micromatch/picomatch.git - 2.3.2,https://github.com/micromatch/picomatch.git - 3.0.2,https://github.com/micromatch/picomatch.git - 4.0.4</p>\n\n</p>\n\n<p></p>\n\n\nStep up your Open Source Security Game with Mend [here](https://www.whitesourcesoftware.com/full_solution_bolt_github)\n</details>","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kleros/vea/issues/452/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kleros/vea/issues/452/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049/events","html_url":"https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049","id":4447059485,"node_id":"I_kwDOAS86yM8AAAABCRC-HQ","number":15049,"title":"@react-router/node: writeReadableStreamToWritable ignores Node writable backpressure","user":{"login":"ianduvall","id":14840469,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0ODQwNDY5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/14840469?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall","html_url":"https://github.com/ianduvall","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ianduvall/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":4775510162,"node_id":"LA_kwDOAS86yM8AAAABHKSAkg","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/labels/pkg:react-router","name":"pkg:react-router","color":"3992ff","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-14T15:16:25Z","updated_at":"2026-05-18T19:03:33Z","closed_at":"2026-05-18T19:03:33Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Reproduction\n\nA runnable reproduction lives in the unit test on the fix PR: [`packages/react-router-node/__tests__/stream-test.ts`](https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/pull/15048/files). It pumps 100 chunks (8 bytes each) into a `Writable` whose `_write` is artificially slow and asserts buffered bytes stay near `highWaterMark`. Without the fix the assertion observes peak buffered bytes near 800 (the entire source) instead of ~24.\n\nStandalone repro that does not depend on the test harness:\n\n```js\nimport { Writable } from \"node:stream\";\nimport { writeReadableStreamToWritable } from \"@react-router/node\";\n\nconst writable = new Writable({\n  highWaterMark: 16,\n  write(_chunk, _enc, cb) {\n    console.log(\"buffered:\", writable.writableLength);\n    setTimeout(cb, 5);\n  },\n});\n\nconst stream = new ReadableStream({\n  start(controller) {\n    for (let i = 0; i < 100; i++) controller.enqueue(new Uint8Array(8));\n    controller.close();\n  },\n});\n\nawait writeReadableStreamToWritable(stream, writable);\n```\n\nObserved: `buffered:` lines print values up to ~800 (the producer never paused).\nExpected: values stay bounded near `highWaterMark + chunkSize` (24).\n\n### System Info\n\n```\nOS:    macOS (darwin 25.5.0 arm64)\nNode:  v24.15.0\nPkg:   @react-router/node 7.15.1\n```\n\nThis is platform-independent. It depends only on Node stream semantics.\n\n### Used Package Manager\n\npnpm\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\n`writeReadableStreamToWritable` should honor the standard Node streams backpressure contract. When `writable.write()` returns `false`, the producer should pause reading from the `ReadableStream` until the writable emits `'drain'`. Buffered bytes on the writable should stay bounded by roughly `highWaterMark + chunkSize`.\n\n### Actual Behavior\n\n`writeReadableStreamToWritable` ignores the boolean return value of `writable.write()` and unconditionally reads the next chunk. When the sink is slower than the source (slow socket, compression middleware throttling, slow disk), chunks accumulate unbounded in the writable's internal buffer. For SSR responses to slow clients this can drive significant server-side memory pressure, since the whole rendered response can sit in the writable buffer regardless of how fast the client can absorb it.\n\nSource: [`packages/react-router-node/stream.ts:4-29`](https://github.com/remix-run/react-router/blob/v7.15.1/packages/react-router-node/stream.ts#L4-L29) on `v7.15.1`:\n\n```ts\nwritable.write(value);\nif (typeof flushable.flush === \"function\") flushable.flush();\n```\n\nNo `drain` await, no return-value check.\n\nFix: #15048\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/remix-run/react-router/issues/15049/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"la